Caroline
Lupini
Editor
Updated:
Mar
3,
2021,
10:50am
Editorial
Note:
Forbes
may
earn
a
commission
on
sales
made
from
partner
links
on
this
page,
but
that
doesn't
affect
our
editors'
opinions
or
evaluations.
Your
Instagram
feed
might
make
it
seem
like
travel
hacking
is
just
for
the
most
frequent
of
flyers.
Guess
again.
It&#8217;s
easier
than
you
think
to
leverage
your
credit
card
rewards
to
snag
award
flights
and
upgrades
using
miles
and
points.
That
said,
be
sure
to
have
your
credit
house
in
order
before
you
start
earning
rewards
because
the
interest
rates
and
fees
will
outweigh
what
you
earn
on
a
monthly
balance.
The
right
card
for
you
is
based
on
your
goals
and
circumstances.
A
couple
spending
towards
a
honeymoon
in
Paris,
France
will
have
different
needs
than
a
family
trying
to
visit
family
in
Paris,
Texas.  Always
do
the
math
for
your
personal
spending
and
consider
how
you
would
use
the
benefits
before
applying
for
a
new
card.
Our
guide
to
the
Best
Travel
Rewards
Credit
Cards
of
2021
is
a
great
place
to
start,
whether
your
plans
take
you
to
the
skies
or
just
down
the
road.
